00:03:14.100 --> 00:03:15.500
You know what an interval is?

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:16.500
yes

00:03:16.700 --> 00:03:17.100
You learned that?

00:03:17.200 --> 00:03:20.000
It's a space between two notes

00:03:20.200 --> 00:03:21.800
and you have only...

00:03:21.900 --> 00:03:23.000
You have to know this,

00:03:23.100 --> 00:03:25.900
that you have only three intervals in your hand,

00:03:26.100 --> 00:03:28.700
only three intervals in your whole hand.

00:03:29.400 --> 00:03:30.500
And we make such a...

00:03:30.600 --> 00:03:31.500
When you look at the music

00:03:31.600 --> 00:03:33.200
you see lots and lots of fingers,

00:03:33.400 --> 00:03:36.800
new fingers, new notes
you never saw before in your life

00:03:37.000 --> 00:03:40.800
and it's only three intervals in the hand.

00:03:40.835 --> 00:03:43.300
So, you go into the notes,

00:03:43.400 --> 00:03:45.000
instead of onto the notes,

00:03:45.100 --> 00:03:46.300
and connect them.

00:03:46.400 --> 00:03:48.900
What are the three intervals, please?

00:03:49.300 --> 00:03:51.700
What are the three intervals, please?

00:03:53.000 --> 00:03:56.000
Well, I call them in my own way,

