At least you know how to prevent...

00:04:56.500 --> 00:04:57.800
Are you with me?

00:04:58.100 --> 00:05:01.700
That's how you teach a beginner

00:05:02.700 --> 00:05:05.100
to have a musical knowledge with the hand

00:05:05.200 --> 00:05:07.700
and not just the first finger is the A,

00:05:07.800 --> 00:05:09.800
the second finger is the...

00:05:10.500 --> 00:05:13.000
no first, second and
you don't even say note names

00:05:13.100 --> 00:05:14.700
first, second, third, fourth fingers,

00:05:15.100 --> 00:05:17.500
which has nothing to do
with music, rhythm...

00:05:17.900 --> 00:05:22.700
or the sense of the space between the notes,

00:05:22.800 --> 00:05:25.200
the important sense of musical sense,

00:05:25.400 --> 00:05:28.500
because the music happens between the notes.

00:05:28.600 --> 00:05:30.000
Does that make sense?
Yes

00:05:30.400 --> 00:05:33.100
In the space, in the swinging intervals

00:05:33.200 --> 00:05:35.400
and if the fingers can't do that,

00:05:35.700 --> 00:05:37.300
then it's in your way,

